#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:2
#: 95f3192c84a244a296aa498f84dda76c
msgid "Emmentaler Block"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:4
#: 4489a368623f4e54a9b3a811c4807904
msgid ""
"The Emmentaler example is a three-stage progression on the same geometry "
"— a :math:`1.0 \\times 1.0 \\times 1.5` block punched with 23 randomly-"
"placed spherical holes (hence the name). The block is clamped at the "
"bottom and subjected to a combined tension / bending / torsion at the "
"top. Three scripts in ``examples/solid/emmentaler/`` solve the same "
"boundary-value problem with progressively richer physics:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:12
#: aa4240b40cd5408d99903d05a16663ab
msgid ""
"**Linear elasticity** (``emmentaler_elasticity.py``) — small strain, "
"single direct solve per load step."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:14
#: 663f4b6213d041529d7fc085573b9d4d
msgid ""
"**Neo-Hookean hyperelasticity** (``emmentaler_hyperelastic.py``) — finite"
" strain, energy minimization."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:16
#: 8ac652bde1de4e049a73547497729e84
msgid ""
"**Phase-field fracture** (``emmentaler_phasefield.py``) — AT1 damage "
"model with staggered displacement / damage solver."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:19
#: 8e3f6389d30548a6b94d9352f2de87c4
msgid ""
"The geometry, BCs, and loading are identical across the three; the script"
" you run determines the constitutive model. This makes Emmentaler a "
"useful \"scaling test\" for solver complexity: the linear-elasticity "
"stage is a sanity check (drops out of any other stage as the small-strain"
" limit), and the phase-field stage is the research-grade endpoint."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:28
#: bb32f7eb6d1c4b469c79e706f621168e
msgid "Shared setup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:30
#: 513212c1beae4fb897980ff55a4bea75
msgid ""
"All three scripts use the same loading: at the top face :math:`z = T`, "
"prescribe displacement"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:33
#: 7d6b66c7b5634194ab7c8990c50422a0
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"u_z &= \\lambda \\cdot 0.010, \\\\\n"
"\\kappa_\\text{bend} &= \\lambda \\cdot 0.014, \\\\\n"
"\\theta_\\text{tors} &= \\lambda \\cdot 0.048 \\;\\text{rad},"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:39
#: 966de114764840099f919ca359b7edfd
msgid ""
"with :math:`\\lambda \\in [0, 1]` ramped over ``--load_steps``. Material "
"defaults are :math:`E = 12000`, :math:`\\nu = 0.3`. The mesh is generated"
" via Gmsh with the holes as boolean cuts; pass ``--h 0.08`` for a fast "
"smoke test, ``--h 0.03`` for a publication mesh."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:47
#: a035bde8fcea4c4ab6610f1a475b4c31
msgid "Stage 1 — linear elasticity"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:49
#: 839226dadd43419fb8e5450f185c694b
msgid ""
"Identical to :doc:`cantilever_beam` in spirit: "
":class:`~tensormesh.LinearElasticityElementAssembler` plus a "
":class:`~tensormesh.Condenser` for the prescribed top displacement, one "
"direct solve per load step."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:58
#: 491e899fb352484e80f4c8dad5221c4e
msgid ""
"Outputs include the displacement field, infinitesimal strain in Voigt "
"form, Cauchy stress, and von Mises equivalent — written to a ``.vtk`` "
"file you can open in ParaView. This is the right stage to use as a "
"baseline when verifying mesh resolution: under a small :math:`\\lambda` "
"the hyperelastic and elastic solutions should agree."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:67
#: 2aeb3506655c4fa08c0efec3cd0495ca
msgid "Stage 2 — Neo-Hookean hyperelasticity"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:69
#: 77db97dc95064baab768dbe207628de2
msgid ""
"The hyperelastic stage replaces the small-strain quadratic energy with "
"the compressible Neo-Hookean strain-energy density"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:72
#: 1ace6f57092042dfabfe5413ace378f1
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\Psi(\\mathbf{F}) \\;=\\;\n"
"\\frac{\\mu}{2} (I_1 - 3)\n"
"- \\mu \\ln J\n"
"+ \\frac{\\lambda}{2} (\\ln J)^2,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:79
#: b988f1c0e4ab4992bbe118b541677851
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"where :math:`\\mathbf{F} = \\mathbf{I} + \\nabla \\mathbf{u}`, :math:`I_1"
" = \\mathrm{tr}(\\mathbf{F}^T \\mathbf{F})`, and :math:`J = \\det "
"\\mathbf{F}`. The total potential :math:`\\Pi(\\mathbf{u}) = "
"\\int_\\Omega \\Psi\\,\\mathrm{d}\\Omega` is minimized with PyTorch's "
"L-BFGS optimizer, with autograd providing the gradient. The class "
"implementing :math:`\\Psi` is the same ``NeoHookeanModel`` you see in "
":doc:`hyperelastic_beam`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:87
#: 2787f335ddbe4ee9a6b48a2a7ee8a1b4
msgid ""
"Incremental loading is essential: the total tension / bending / torsion "
"is split into ``--load_steps`` increments, and each step warm-starts "
"L-BFGS from the previous step's solution. Without incrementation, L-BFGS "
"often fails to find a basin at full load."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:96
#: 43d140da21e24896993f293fda1e5f8f
msgid ""
"Output is the same as Stage 1 but with **Green-Lagrange strain** and "
"**Cauchy stress** (computed from the converged deformation gradient, not "
"the small-strain approximations)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:102
#: 9f2704c0edc24e2ab5fcbb33af32450d
msgid "Stage 3 — phase-field fracture (AT1)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:104
#: e2e7579d77d9427da2a4ece7c323a27d
msgid ""
"The phase-field stage adds a scalar damage variable :math:`\\alpha \\in "
"[0, 1]` (0 = pristine, 1 = fully cracked) to the unknowns. The total "
"energy is"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:108
#: 669b95ecd70545039c860359b2b11fa9
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\mathcal{E}(\\mathbf{u}, \\alpha) \\;=\\;\n"
"\\int_\\Omega g(\\alpha)\\, \\Psi^{+}(\\mathbf{F}) \\,\\mathrm{d}\\Omega\n"
"\\;+\\;\n"
"\\int_\\Omega \\Psi^{-}(\\mathbf{F}) \\,\\mathrm{d}\\Omega\n"
"\\;+\\;\n"
"\\frac{G_c}{c_w} \\int_\\Omega\n"
"\\left(\\frac{w(\\alpha)}{\\ell} + \\ell\\, |\\nabla \\alpha|^2 \\right)\n"
"\\,\\mathrm{d}\\Omega,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:119
#: 1ff57d0c54414bb98d974f14d98cdea7
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"with the AT1 dissipation function :math:`w(\\alpha) = \\alpha`, the Amor "
"split into tensile / compressive parts :math:`\\Psi^{+} / \\Psi^{-}`, and"
" the regularization length scale :math:`\\ell`. The script solves it with"
" a **staggered** alternating minimization:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:125
#: 369842fc72f848e89cf4d994cf6d5dee
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"fix :math:`\\alpha`, minimize :math:`\\mathcal{E}` over "
":math:`\\mathbf{u}` (LBFGS),"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:127
#: b482541c39ea48249ae3aba644f2cd4e
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"fix :math:`\\mathbf{u}`, minimize :math:`\\mathcal{E}` over "
":math:`\\alpha` with the irreversibility constraint :math:`\\alpha \\geq "
"\\alpha^{n-1}` enforced by projection (projected LBFGS)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:132
#: 03b10b05b6fb42f190ddca38c5b0ced6
msgid ""
"Repeat until both fields converge, then take the next load step. This is "
"the standard recipe in the phase-field-fracture literature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:145
#: 087d929e169e451abade5c639abc87d0
#, python-format
msgid ""
"The AT1 model has a sharp elastic phase before damage initiates, so most "
"of the load steps are uneventful — the interesting picture is in the last"
" 10–20 % of the loading where cracks nucleate near the holes and "
"propagate through the block."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/emmentaler.rst:150
#: eb791aa8aff644fb8e61fe3e91ccb456
msgid ""
"*(figure: damage field on the deformed mesh near peak load; will be added"
" in a follow-up)*"
msgstr ""

